text: Antonio Imbert Barrera (December 3, 1920 - May 31, 2016) was a politician of the Dominican Republic. He served as President of the Dominican Republic from May 7, 1965 until August 30, 1965. The president before him was Pedro Bartolomé Benoit. The president after him was Héctor García Godoy. ==References== Category:1920 births Category:2016 deaths Category:North American military people Category:Presidents of the Dominican Republic
